headline: WEF clears founder Schwab of wrongdoing; appoints interim co-chairs
summary: (Reuters) -The World Economic Forum closed an investigation on its founder Klaus Schwab on Friday, clearing him of any wrongdoing, and appointed BlackRock CEO Larry Fink and Roche Holding's vice-chair Andre Hoffmann as interim co-chairs of its board.  The Geneva-based organisation had launched an investigation in April into 87-year-old Schwab following a whistleblower letter alleging misconduct.  The probe was announced a day after Schwab resigned as chairman.
